A rule that loads a static configuration file from disk and emits its
contents as text. The file path is declared in the source as a literal
resource — auditing the binary tells you exactly which file the program
can open. Reading a file the rule does not declare is impossible: the
verifier rejects unknown read() targets at compile time, and the binary
contains no other open() syscalls beyond the declared resource.

If the file cannot be opened (missing, permission denied, FS error) the
process exits with status 1 — the on_read_error: abort policy makes
silent-failure impossible for slice 1. Recovery is the operator's job
(systemd restart, alerting), not the binary's.
